description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic individual with a commitment to cancer care to work with the Macmillan Clinical Nurse Specialist Teams in the role of Cancer Support Worker for one year. This post is predominantly with the lung team but there will be the required to work across disease site teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is currently based cross site at both the Royal Sussex County and Princess Royal Hospitals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide support, care and assessment of patients throughout their cancer journey. This will involve a combination of administrative work, (ensuring appropriate information is available for patients and healthcare staff), and patient contact, primarily by phone and email with some face to face . The MSW is often the first point of contact for patients and carers and will frequently be triaging their information needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This special individual, with excellent communication skills, will work alongside the Clinical Nurse Specialists and other members of the multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term (1 year) fulltime position working Monday to Friday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Nicki Colburn&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Macmillan Nurse Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address bsuh.maclungcns.patients@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01273 696955 ext 3803&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Randall&lt;/p&gt;
